{"title":"2017 interim frameworks for teacher assessment at the end of key stage 1","public_updated_at":"2016-12-15T16:01:48Z","details":{"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>These interim frameworks are to support teachers in making robust and accurate judgements for pupils at the end of key stage 1 in 2017. The interim teacher assessment frameworks are for 2016 to 2017 only. The Department for Education is evaluating options for future years.</p>\n\n<p>The interim frameworks set out the standard(s) a pupil will be assessed against at the end of the key stage for reading, writing, mathematics and science.</p>\n\n<p>To show that pupils have met the standard, teachers will need to have evidence that a pupil demonstrates consistent attainment of all the statements within the standard.</p>\n</div>","change_history":[{"public_timestamp":"2016-12-15T16:01:48.000+00:00","note":"Key principles of the interim framework for key stage 1 writing have been updated to reflect the optional nature of the key stage 1 English grammar, punctuation and spelling test."},{"public_timestamp":"2016-07-14T12:45:00.000+01:00","note":"First published."}],"documents":["<section class=\"attachment embedded\" id=\"attachment_1856333\">\n  <div class=\"attachment-thumb\">\n      <a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"thumbnail\" href=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/576179/2017_interim_teacher_assessment_frameworks_at_the_end_of_key_stage_1_V2_PDFa.pdf\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/576179/thumbnail_2017_interim_teacher_assessment_frameworks_at_the_end_of_key_stage_1_V2_PDFa.pdf.png\" /></a>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"attachment-details\">\n    <h2 class=\"title\"><a href=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/576179/2017_interim_teacher_assessment_frameworks_at_the_end_of_key_stage_1_V2_PDFa.pdf\">2017 Interim teacher assessment frameworks at the end of key stage 1</a></h2>\n    <p class=\"metadata\">\n        <spa